6\u03bd \u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c0\u03ac\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2<br />\n<br />\n\u039f \u0391\u03a1\u03a7\u0399\u0395\u03a0\u0399\u03a3\u039a\u039f\u03a0\u039f\u03a3<br />\n\u039f \u0391\u039c\u0395\u03a1\u0399\u039a\u0397\u03a3 [[Archbishop Iakovos of America|\u0399\u0391\u039a\u03a9\u0392\u039f\u03a3]]\"<ref name=GRKCATHEDRAL/>|group=note}}</small>\n* <small>2000 Five-alarm fire entirely guts interior of Church.<ref>Hamida Ghafour. ''Church Fire Leaves Greek Community in Shock.'' [[The Globe and Mail]]. Tuesday April 4, 2000. Page A20.</ref><ref>Robert Arnold and Peter Vogel. ''\"[http://www.cci-icc.gc.ca/about-apropos/nb/nb26/fire-feu-eng.aspx CCI Responds to Fire at the Greek Orthodox Cathedral].\"'' [[Canadian Conservation Institute|CCI]] Newsletter, No. 26, November 2000.</ref><ref>''\"Landmark church goes up in flames, dozens of firefighters bring blaze under control.\"'' [[The Canadian Press|Canadian Press Newswire]]. Toronto:Apr 3, 2000.</ref></small>\n* <small>2002 A [[Byzantine Revival architecture|new Byzantine]]-style church is opened within the old [[Romanesque Revival architecture|Romanesque building]].<ref>Jim Wilkes. ''\"Church reborn from ashes: Greek Orthodox cathedral to reopen after blaze in 2000.\"'' [[Toronto Star]]. Thursday June 27, 2002. Page B04.</ref><ref>Lighthall, WD. ''\"Rebuilding of church a true labour of love.\"'' Daily Commercial News and Construction Record. Mar 26, 2002. Vol.75, Iss.60, p.A1,A5.</ref>{{#tag:ref|The exquisite Byzantine Icons in the Altar were painted by the master icon painter Father Theodore Koufos, while the Baroque wooden iconostasis, Altar Table, Cantor\u2019s Stand and Bishop\u2019s Throne were hand-carved by Master Wood Sculptor Stylianos Kavroulakis of Crete. The Cathedral holds over 850 seated worshippers, and has parking facilities for 50 cars.|group=note}}</small>\n* <small>2006 ''Odyssey Montessori School - Sorauren Campus'' is established.<ref>''[http://odysseymontessori.com/?page_id=68 Odyssey Montessori School - Sorauren Campus].'' Odyssey Montessori School. Retrieved: 1 June 2016.</ref></small>\n* <small>2011 Annunciation Greek Orthodox Cathedral celebrates its 50th year anniversary.</small>\n| [[File:Annunciation Of The Virgin Mary Greek Orthodox Cathedral (Toronto).JPG|100px]]\n|-\n| St Demetrios Greek Orthodox Church\n| [[Thorncliffe Park]]<br />\n| 1962\n|\n* <small>1962 Saint Demetrios Greek Orthodox Church and the attached Polymenakion Cultural Centre built.</small>\n:* <small>The Cultural centre provides: head offices for GCT; an office for the priest and the church administrators; classrooms for Sunday school students; and multipurpose workshops for extra-curricular, cultural and religious activities.</small>\n* <small>1975 Painting of the church was completed by Mr. G. Papastamatiou.</small>\n* <small>Living Orthodoxy. (Adult Religious Education ministry of St Demetrios Greek Orthodox Church).</small>\n| [[File:St Demetrios Greek Orthodox Church.JPG|100px]]\n|-\n| All Saints Greek Orthodox Community\n| [[Bayview Village]]<br />\n| 1963,<br />1966\n|\n* <small>1963 North Toronto Greek Orthodox Parish (operating as All Saints Greek Orthodox Church) is founded, the first in the city of [[North York]].</small>\n* <small>1966 First service celebrated in its new building in March 1966.</small>\n* <small>First Greek Church in Ontario to conduct its services in both Greek and English.</small>\n| [[File:All Saints Greek Orthodox Community, Toronto.jpg|100px]]\n|-\n| St. Nicholas Greek Orthodox Community\n| [[L'Amoreaux]]\n| 1971,<br />1983<ref name=ST-NICK-SCAR-GO>''[http://www.saintnicholasgochurch.org/parish-history/ Parish History - Saint Nicholas Greek Orthodox Church].'' Toronto, Ontario. Accessed 2017-04-12.</ref>\n|\n* <small>May 15, 1994 - St. Nicholas was [[Consecrations in Eastern Christianity#Consecration of a church|consecrated]] by His Eminence Metropolitan Archbishop Sotirios of Toronto (Canada).<ref name=ST-NICK-SCAR-GO/></small>\n* <small